2014-12-12  kstn  <kastian@mail.ru>

	DATE: New date implementation
	IMPORTANT

	Now $DAY, $MONTH, $YEAR, $MOON are ints, so if you want string, you
	should use:

	day    - $(Ordial $DAY)	- 1st, 2nd, ...
	month  - $(MonthString $MONTH) - After-Frost, Marrsuckur, ...
	       	 $(MonthTrivia $MONTH) - "1st Month of the Year\n This is the coldest and darkest month of the year. Stay in, stay warm.", ...

	year   - $(Ordial $YEAR) - 1st, 2nd, ...
	moon   - ${MOON_STR[$MOON]} - "New Moon","Growing Crescent", ...

	Moon changes:

	"New Moon" is the same that "Old Moon", so I've removed "Old Moon"

	This implementation breaks Almanac, so Almanac.sh should be rewrited

